      <title>Barcelona terror attack claims at least 13 lives</title>
      <description><![CDATA[Visit http://archive.nextanimationstudio.com or contact inquiries@nextanimation.com.tw to license this or any News Direct videoFor story suggestions please contact tips@nextanimation.com.twRESTRICTIONS: NONEAt least 13 people were killed and more than 100 others injured in a terrorist attack in Barcelona on Thursday.A white Fiat van drove into pedestrians at high speed on Las Ramblas, a popular pedestrianized boulevard that runs through the heart of the city, the Guardian reported.The van traveled for around 500 meters before stopping at a newspaper stand. The driver escaped on foot.Citizens of at least 24 different countries are among the victims, including one Belgian and three Germans. ISIS claimed responsibility for the attack. Police in Spain said the attack was linked to an explosion on Wednesday night at a house in Alcanar, 200 km south of Barcelona, in which one person died and at least seven others were injured, according to the Independent.Police believe the explosion may have been part of a larger terror plot that went wrong.The Barcelona atrocity was followed by a second attack on Thursday night in the town of Cambrils, 120 km south of the city.Terrorist suspects drove an Audi A3 into pedestrians in Cambrils. Five men reportedly wearing explosive belts were later shot dead by police.RUNDOWN SHOWS:1. Location of Barcelona2. Van drives into pedestrians on Las Ramblas3. Route of van on Las Ramblas4. Driver escapes5. Location of explosion in Alcanar; location of Cambrils6. Car drives at pedestrians in Cambrils; five suspects killedVOICEOVER (in English): SOURCES: The Guardian, BBC Newshttps://www.theguardian.com/world/2017/aug/17/van-crashes-into-crowd-of-people-barcelona-las-ramblashttps://www.theguardian.com/world/live/2017/aug/17/barcelona-attack-van-driven-into-crowd-in-las-ramblas-districthttp://www.bbc.com/news/world-europe-40964242 ***For story suggestions please contact tips@nextanimation.com.twFor technical and editorial 