      <title>Saturn's moon found to contain key elements of life</title>
      <description><![CDATA[Contact inquiries@nextanimation.com to license this or any News Direct videoFor story suggestions please contact tips@nextanimation.com.twRESTRICTIONS: NONENew research suggests that Saturn's moon Titan may contain the key elements of life.Using data from NASA's Cassini satellite, one study found that the Titan's upper atmosphere is home to carbon chain anions, reported the Smithsonian Mag. These serve as a stepping stone to more labyrinthine molecules that can develop life, reported Mic.Separately, another study in found vinyl cyanide in Titan's atmosphere. Scientists speculate that this forms the the outer wall of a cell and protects the biochemistry that takes place within, reported Universe Today.Titan's atmosphere is some of the most complex observed by astronomers and these studies further bolster the idea the moon maybe home to organic life. The studies were published was published last month in The Astrophysical Journal Letters and Science Advances.RUNDOWN SHOWS:1. NASA Cassini spacecraft observing Titan2. Carbon chain anions in Titan atmosphere3. Vinyl Cyanide in Titan atmosphere4. Vinyl Cyanide with cell.VOICEOVER (in English): "Using data from NASA's Cassini satellite, one study found that the Titan's upper atmosphere is home to carbon chain anions. "These serve as a stepping stone to more labyrinthine molecules that can develop life.""Separately another study found vinyl cyanide in Titan's atmosphere.""Scientists speculate that this forms the the outer wall of a cell and protects the biochemistry that takes place within."SOURCES: The Astrophysical Journal Letters, Science Advances, TechRadar, Smithsonian.com, Mic, Universe Today, The Conversation, University College Londonhttp://iopscience.iop.org/article/10.3847/2041-8213/aa7851http://advances.sciencemag.org/content/3/7/e1700022http://www.techradar.com/news/is-there-life-on-titanhttp://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/new-studies-bolster-case-habitability-titan-180964258/htt