      <title>Iranian drones comes within 100 feet of U.S. fighter jet</title>
      <description><![CDATA[Contact inquiries@nextanimation.com to license this or any News Direct videoFor story suggestions please contact tips@nextanimation.com.twRESTRICTIONS: NONEAn Iranian drone nearly collided with a U.S. Navy fighter jet over the Persian Gulf on Tuesday.The U.S. Navy F/A-18E Super Hornet was preparing to land on the USS Nimitz aircraft carrier, the Washington Post reported.The fighter jet was circling in a holding pattern, when an Iranian QOM-1 drone came within 100 feet below and 200 feet to the side of it, according to CNN.The pilot of the U.S. jet was forced to make an evasive maneuver to avoid a collision. The Navy made repeated radio warning calls for the drone to keep away that were unanswered.U.S. forces had 35 hostile interactions with Iranian forces last year, up from 23 in 2015, according to the Pentagon. RUNDOWN SHOWS:1.  Location of Persian Gulf2. U.S. Super Hornet jet flying in holding pattern above USS Nimitz aircraft carrier3. Iranian drone flies within 100 feet of Super Hornet4. Super Hornet makes radio warning call, makes evasive maneuverVOICEOVER (in English): "The incident took place in the Persian Gulf on Tuesday, when a U.S. Navy F/A-18E Super Hornet circled in a holding pattern above the USS Nimitz aircraft carrier as it prepared to land.""According to U.S. officials, an Iranian drone came within 100 feet below and 200 feet to the side of the Super Hornet.""Officials said the pilot of the U.S. jet was forced to make an evasive maneuver and the Navy made repeated radio warning calls for the drone to keep away that were unanswered."SOURCES: Washington Post, CNNhttp://wapo.st/2vhLNp3http://cnn.it/2ulToEn***For story suggestions please contact tips@nextanimation.com.twFor technical and editorial support, please contact:Asia: +61 2 93 73 1841Europe: +44 20 7542 7599Americas and Latam: +1 800 738 8377]]></description>
