      <title>North Korea has created miniaturized warheads for its ICBM-class missiles</title>
      <description><![CDATA[Contact inquiries@nextanimation.com to license this or any News Direct videoFor story suggestions please contact tips@nextanimation.com.twRESTRICTIONS: NONEU.S. President Donald Trump is warning North Korea of 'fire and fury' after a Washington Post report revealed Pyongyang has already produced miniaturized warheads for its ICBM-class missiles.A US Defense Intelligence Agency report leaked to the Washington Post says North Korea has successfully created miniaturized warhead for its intercontinental ballistic missiles and it has up to 60 nuclear warheads in its arsenal."North Korea best not make any more threats to the United States. They will be met with fire and fury like the world has never seen. He has been very threatening  beyond a normal statement  and as I said, they will be met with fire, fury and, frankly, power the likes of which the world has never seen before," President Trump said in an event on Tuesday afternoon.North Korea now has missiles with ranges between 180 to 7,200 miles. The country conducted two ICBM tests last month, which shows its potential to hit most of the continental U.S.In a response, the United Nations imposed its toughest sanctions yet on North Korea, banning the country from exports and limiting investments, which could potentially reduce a third of the country's $3 billion worth of export revenue.However, North Korea said the sanctions would not stop it from developing nuclear weapons and threatened to make the U.S. to pay the price.RUNDOWN SHOWS:1. North Korea's miniaturized warhead fitted on its ICBM missile2. Ranges of North Korea's missiles3. Estimated number of nuclear warheads of North Korea, Russia and U.S.VOICEOVER (in English): "A US Defense Intelligence Agency report says North Korea has successfully created miniaturized warhead for its intercontinental ballistic missiles.""The country now has missiles that reportedly range between between 180 to 7,200 miles.""The agency report also estimates that North Korea has up to 60 nuclear warheads in its arsenal. Russia and United States still have the largest amount of nuclear warheads in the world, estimated at 7,000 and 6,800 respectively."SOURCES: Washington Post, The Telegraph, BBC, ABC Newshttps://www.washingtonpost.com/world/national-security/north-korea-now-making-missile-ready-nuclear-weapons-us-analysts-say/2017/08/08/e14b882a-7b6b-11e7-9d08-b79f191668ed_story.html?utm_term=.ebbc820cd9adhttp://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2017/08/08/north-korea-has-produced-miniaturised-nuclear-warhead-fit-inside/http://www.bbc.com/news/world-us-canada-40869319http://www.bbc.com/news/world-asia-40846959http://abcnews.go.com/Politics/trump-north-korea-met-fire-fury-threats-continue/story?id=49097627***For story suggestions please contact tips@nextanimation.com.twFor technical and editorial support, please contact:Asia: +61 2 93 73 1841Europe: +44 20 7542 7599Americas and Latam: +1 800 738 8377]]></description>
