      <title>British supermarket equips ATMS with traceable spray gel</title>
      <description><![CDATA[Contact inquiries@nextanimation.com to license this or any News Direct videoFor story suggestions please contact tips@nextanimation.com.twRESTRICTIONS: NONEBritish supermarket The Co-operative has outfitted of their ATMs in 2,500 stores with a traceable spray gel to deter would-be criminals.Each sprayer has it's own forensic identifier, and only a speck of this is needed from the suspect to match it to the ATM, reported the Independent. The gel is visible under an ultraviolet black light.If someone tries to break into an ATM, their clothes and face are sprayed with the gel.Developer company Smart Water told the Guardian that the gel can be traced up to five years after being sprayed.The technology reportedly reduced ATM theft by up to 90 percent in test areas in 2016. RUNDOWN SHOWS:1.  Amount of Co-op ATMS in UK with spray gel2. Thief being sprayed with gel3. UV light scanning thief4. Officer scanning thief with UV lightVOICEOVER (in English): "The Co-Op, a British supermarket, has outfitted ATMs in 2,500 stores with a traceable spray gel to deter would-be criminals.""When someone tries to break into an ATM, their clothes and face are sprayed with the gel.""Each sprayer has it's own forensic identifier, and only a speck of this is needed from the suspect to match it to the ATM.""The gel is visible under an ultraviolet black light.""Developer company Smart Water say the gel can be traced up to five years after being sprayed."SOURCES: SmartWater, Devon Live, The Independent, The Guardianhttps://www.smartwater.comwww.devonlive.com/cash-machines-thieves-will-end-up-like-this-if-they-mess-with-atms/story-30468672-detail/story.htmlhttp://www.independent.co.uk/news/business/news/co-op-group-cash-points-smartwater-gel-criminals-police-trace-co-operative-bank-a7874601.htmlhttps://www.theguardian.com/business/2017/aug/03/co-operative-atm-cash-machine-thieves-sprayed-traceable-gel-crime***For story suggestions please contact tips@nextanimation.com.t