      <description><![CDATA[Visit http://archive.nextanimationstudio.com or contact inquiries@nextanimation.com.tw to license this or any News Direct videoFor story suggestions please contact tips@nextanimation.com.twRESTRICTIONS: NONETen sailors were missing and five others injured after a U.S. warship collided with an oil tanker.The USS John S. McCain destroyer collided with the Liberian-registered Alnic MC merchant ship east of the straits of Malacca and Singapore in the early hours of Monday.The U.S. warship sustained damage to its aft port (rear left) side. The ship was flooding in several places, and had limited propulsion and electrical power, U.S. Navy sources told CNN.Singapore scrambled ships and helicopters to begin a search and rescue mission.The USS John McCain was sailing toward Singapore on its own power, according to the Guardian.The incident comes just two months after seven U.S. sailors died when the USS Fitzgerald collided with a container ship off Japan in June.  RUNDOWN SHOWS:1. Location of collision between USS John S. McCain and Alnic MC oil tanker2. Collision between USS John S. McCain and Alnic MC (Liberian flag)3. USS John McCain hit by flooding, limited propulsion and electrical power4. Ten sailors missing; five injuredVOICEOVER (in English): "The USS John S. McCain destroyer collided with an oil tanker east of Singapore in the early hours of Monday.""The U.S. warship sustained damage to its aft port  or rear left  side in the collision with the Liberian-registered vessel.""According to the U.S. Navy, the USS John McCain was fighting flooding in several places, and had limited propulsion and electrical power.""Ten U.S. sailors were missing and five were injured."SOURCES: The Guardian, CNNhttp://bit.ly/2xgTiKThttp://cnn.it/2iiB1Kz ***For story suggestions please contact tips@nextanimation.com.twFor technical and editorial support, please contact:Asia: +61 2 93 73 1841Europe: +44 20 7542 7599Americas and Latam: +1 800 738 8377]]></descriptio